Description: Do not treat warnings as errors in the vendored Fast DDS library
 Fedora injects -Werror, turning benign upstream warnings (unused-but-set
 variables in CacheChange.hpp, the bundled sqlite3 amalgamation, etc.) into hard
 errors on Fedora's GCC. Apply -Wno-error as a target_compile_options on the
 fastdds library (after add_library) so it overrides the inherited -Werror for
 that target. Upstream keeps -Werror only in its own CI.
Origin: vendor-specific
Forwarded: not-needed, downstream packaging relaxation of warnings-as-errors
Last-Update: 2026-06-03
--- a/src/cpp/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-02 21:25:48.552995167 -0500
+++ b/src/cpp/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-02 21:25:48.563515504 -0500
@@ -118,6 +118,10 @@
 
 #Create library
 add_library(${PROJECT_NAME} ${${PROJECT_NAME}_source_files})
+# Fedora injects -Werror; relax it for this vendored library target so benign
+# upstream warnings do not fail the build (applied as a target option so it
+# overrides the inherited -Werror).
+target_compile_options(${PROJECT_NAME} PRIVATE $<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX>:-Wno-error>)
 set_target_properties(${PROJECT_NAME} PROPERTIES
     VERSION ${PROJECT_VERSION}
     SOVERSION ${PROJECT_VERSION_MAJOR}.${PROJECT_VERSION_MINOR}
